âœ… Armstrong Number Check
An Armstrong number of k digits is a number such that the sum of each digit raised to the power k equals the number itself.

ğŸ”¸ Java Code

class Solution {
    static boolean armstrongNumber(int n) {
        int k = String.valueOf(n).length();
        int sum = 0;
        int num = n;

        while (n > 0) {
            int ld = n % 10;
            sum += Math.pow(ld, k);
            n = n / 10;
        }

        return sum == num;
    }
}

ğŸ”¹ Whatâ€™s happening?

Count digits k

For each digit, raise it to power k and add to sum

Compare the final sum with the original number






ğŸ”¸ Python Code
class Solution:
    def armstrongNumber(self, n):
        k = len(str(n))
        sum = 0
        num = n

        while n > 0:
            last = n % 10
            sum += last ** k
            n = n // 10

        return sum == num

